  "original_title": "\u0da2\u0dbd \u0d9c\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dc0 1 \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dcf \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0da7 \u0d89\u0dc4\u0dc5\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Water charges up from 1st",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A senior official of the National Water Supply and Drainage Board said that it has been decided to increase the water charges from September 1.",
        "Accordingly, the water tariff will be increased by 70 to 90 percent and the service fee will be increased by a higher percentage, said the official.",
        "The official said that he did his best to implement the increase in water charges in such a way that it does not burden the people and also paid attention to the low income earners.",
        "The official said that although the cabinet approved to increase the water tariff from 15th August, it has been decided to implement it from 15th September. He also mentioned that it will be implemented from the 15th because it has to be charged.",
        "The water supply service charge is determined according to the number of water consumption units and the service charge was earlier ranging from Rs.50 to Rs.1600.",
        "Water Supply Minister Mr. Keheliya Rambukwella has signed the gazette announcement related to the increase in water charges and the announcement was scheduled to be issued today (26) night."
      ],
